---
---
<section class="stories" id="stories" aria-labelledby="stories-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="stories-inner">

      <div class="stories-left">
        <h2 class="stories-lead">The stories that inspire this film.</h2>

        <div class="stories-list">

          <!-- Ryan Dressler -->
          <article class="story-entry">
            <img
              class="story-photo"
              src="/images/ryan-dressler.webp"
              alt="Ryan Dressler in Ohio"
              width="160"
              height="160"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="story-text">
              <h3 class="story-name">Ryan Dressler</h3>
              <p class="story-body">
                Ryan Dressler runs the numbers for a living. He converted sixty acres in Ohio,
                and the fireflies returned, along with the Baltimore orioles and
                a pair of trumpeter swans. As he puts it: the first half of his life was spent
                lobbying for impact investing, and he would like to spend the second half
                lobbying for nature.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- Sara Weaner Cooper -->
          <article class="story-entry">
            <img
              class="story-photo"
              src="/images/sara-weaner-cooper.webp"
              alt="Sara Weaner Cooper's front yard meadow in Pennsylvania"
              width="160"
              height="160"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="story-text">
              <h3 class="story-name">Sara Weaner Cooper</h3>
              <p class="story-body">
                Sara converted the front lawn of her first house in Pennsylvania. She spent two
                years working with the existing turf rather than tearing it out, and put a small
                sign in the yard so the neighbors would know what was coming. One morning in May,
                the first partridge pea pushed through the grass.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- Victor DeMasi -->
          <article class="story-entry">
            <img
              class="story-photo"
              src="/images/victor-demasi.webp"
              alt="Victor DeMasi, Connecticut meadow steward"
              width="160"
              height="160"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="story-text">
              <h3 class="story-name">Victor DeMasi</h3>
              <p class="story-body">
                Victor DeMasi has counted the butterflies in his Connecticut meadow every Fourth
                of July for twenty-eight years. In the mid-nineties he counted five hundred. Last
                year he counted two hundred and fifty.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- David Kaye -->
          <article class="story-entry">
            <img
              class="story-photo"
              src="/images/david-kaye.webp"
              alt="David Kaye at Nod Hill meadow, Connecticut"
              width="160"
              height="160"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="story-text">
              <h3 class="story-name">David Kaye</h3>
              <p class="story-body">
                David Kaye did not build his meadow to make a point. The strip of land beside
                the brewery was going to become an eyesore, so Nod Hill turned it into the view
                from the beer garden and the filter for the river beside it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- Doug Tallamy -->
          <article class="story-entry">
            <img
              class="story-photo"
              src="/images/doug-tallamy.webp"
              alt="Doug Tallamy, University of Delaware"
              width="160"
              height="160"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="story-text">
              <h3 class="story-name">Doug Tallamy</h3>
              <p class="story-body">
                Doug Tallamy watched a bulldozer bury the pond he grew up next to when he was
                in the third grade. He has spent the rest of his life explaining what is lost
                when the ordinary living things disappear &mdash; and how quickly they return when
                the land is given back to them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

        </div><!-- /.stories-list -->

        <p class="stories-closing">
          These are the people whose stories inspire this film. If your own land
          has a version of this story,{' '}
          <a
            href="mailto:meadowfilm.hello@gmail.com"
            class="stories-link"
          >we would be glad to hear it</a>.
        </p>
      </div><!-- /.stories-left -->

      <div class="stories-right">
        <img
          class="img-stories"
          src="/images/meadow-goldenrod-autumn-pa.webp"
          alt="Goldenrod meadow in autumn, Pennsylvania"
          width="960"
          height="1280"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          class="img-stories"
          src="/images/meadow-wildflowers-northfork.webp"
          alt="Native wildflower meadow, North Fork"
          width="960"
          height="640"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>

    </div><!-- /.stories-inner -->
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stories {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0;
  }

  .stories-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 2fr;
    gap: var(--space-20);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .stories-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.35;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .stories-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  .story-entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .story-photo {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: linear-gradient(155deg, #2e5028 0%, #4A6741 100%);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .story-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .story-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .stories-closing {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.45;
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  .stories-link {
    color: var(--color-earth);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-earth);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: opacity var(--duration-fast);
  }

  .stories-link:hover,
  .stories-link:focus-visible {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .stories-link:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-earth);
    outline-offset: 3px;
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .stories-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .img-stories {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    max-height: 640px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .stories-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .stories-right {
      position: static;
      order: -1;
    }

    .img-stories {
      max-height: 320px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .story-entry {
      grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .story-photo {
      width: 64px;
      height: 64px;
    }
  }
</style>
